article.headline: Liberty 78, High Point 63
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Kyle Ohman matched his career high with 26 points to lead Liberty to a 78-63 victory over High Point on Tuesday night. Ohman hit five 3-pointers and was 9 of 13 from the field as the Flames (15-7, 6-4 Big South Conference) won for the fifth time in six games. Nick Barbour scored 21 points for High Point (5-15, 1-9), which has lost six consecutive games. Ohman keyed Liberty's decisive first-half run with seven points, two assists, two rebounds and a block, helping the Flames increase a 29-27 lead with 7:38 remaining in the first half to a 41-29 advantage with 3:30 left. Liberty was 13 of 28 from the 3-point line (46.4 percent). Anthony Smith scored 23 points for the Flames and Seth Curry added 16 points and 10 rebounds. Jesse Sanders had nine rebounds and nine assists. Eugene Harris added 17 points for High Point.
